pener">Resistance Band Tricep Pushdown</a></td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3–5 x 4–6</td><td>1 minute</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">5-Day Workout Split Push Day</figcaption></figure>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Day 5: Pull</h3>



<p>A 5-day pull split is a highly effective routine targeting the upper-body muscles using pulling movements. This split mainly targets the back, biceps, and shoulder muscles. These upper-body strength exercises help promote balanced muscle strength and development, improve posture, and <a href="https://academic.oup.com/aje/article/187/5/1093/4557909?login=false" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">reduce lower back pain</a>.&nbsp;</p>



<p>It allows for adequate recovery between sessions and can be tailored to individual goals. This makes it a versatile choice for building a well-rounded physique and optimizing upper-body functional performance.</p>



